commit 5e53092b4ddf0d13463471741715657158af4be7
Author: Ben Nasraoui <nasraouiprojects@gmail.com>
Date:   Mon Mar 30 11:22:31 2026 +1000

    feat: provider command execution engine (noscope-6a9)
    
    Implement execute_provider_command() that bridges all existing policy building
    blocks in provider_exec.rs to actual subprocess execution.
    
    Rules covered:
    - NS-068: Spawns with build_sandboxed_env() as base environment
    - NS-036: Checks stdout against MAX_STDOUT_BYTES (1 MiB)
    - NS-040: Captures/truncates stderr, redacts known token values
    - NS-035: Timeout enforcement via SIGTERM then SIGKILL after grace period
    - NS-009: Parses stdout through parse_provider_output()
    - NS-010: Maps exit codes through interpret_provider_exit()
    
    Key design decisions:
    - Concurrent stdout/stderr reading via tokio::spawn to prevent pipe buffer
      deadlock when child writes more than 64KB
    - Returns ProviderExecResult with all execution outcomes (timeout, oversized
      stdout, parse failures, non-zero exit)
    - Added io-util feature to tokio for AsyncReadExt

